description: Canamex Gold Corp. engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mining properties. Its flagship property is the Bruner gold project, which comprises 179 unpatented and 27 patented mining claims covering a total of approximately 3,520 acres located in central Nevada, the United States. The company was formerly known as Canamex Resources Corp. and changed its name to Canamex Gold Corp. in November 2017. Canamex Gold Corp. was incorporated in 1987 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
